SIMPLE: utopia
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Utopia
<hw>U*to"pi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. not +
<?/ a place.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>An imaginary island, represented by Sir Thomas More,
in a work called <ets>Utopia</ets>, as enjoying the greatest perfection
in politics, laws, and the like. See <er>Utopia</er>, in the Dictionary
of Noted Names in Fiction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, any place or state of ideal
perfection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Utopian</ent>⟦br⟧
